quran[62]{c,v,t}:
  53,1,By the star when it goes down
  53,2,Your companion is neither astray nor being misled
  53,3,Nor does he say anything of his own volition
  53,4,It is no less than inspiration sent down to him
  53,5,He was taught by one mighty in power
  53,6,"Endued with wisdom, for he appeared"
  53,7,While he was in the highest part of the horizon
  53,8,Then he approached and came closer
  53,9,And was at a distance of only two bow-lengths or nearer
  53,10,So God conveyed the inspiration to His servant which He meant to convey
  53,11,His heart in no way falsified that which he saw
  53,12,Will you then dispute with him concerning what he saw
  53,13,For indeed he saw him at a second descent
  53,14,Near the lotus-tree beyond which none may pass
  53,15,Near is the garden of abode
  53,16,"Behold, the lotus-tree was shrouded"
  53,17,"His sight never deviated, nor did it go wrong"
  53,18,"For truly he saw the signs of his Lord, the Greatest"
  53,19,Have you seen Lat and ‘Uzza
  53,20,"And another, the third, Manat"
  53,21,"What, for you the male, and for Him, the female"
  53,22,"Behold, that would indeed be a division unfair"
  53,23,"These are nothing but names which you have made up, you and your fathers, for which God has sent down no authority. They follow nothing but speculation, and what their own soul’s desire. Even though there has already come to them guidance from their Lord"
  53,24,"No, will human beings have everything they pursue"
  53,25,But it is to God that the end and the beginning belong
  53,26,"However many angels there are in the heavens, their intercession will avail them nothing, except after God has given permission to whom He pleases, and that they are acceptable to Him"
  53,27,"Those who do not believe in the hereafter, name the angels with female names"
  53,28,"But they cannot know. They follow nothing but speculation, and speculation avails nothing against truth"
  53,29,"Therefore turn away from those who turn away from Our message, and desire nothing but the life of the present"
  53,30,"That is as far as their knowledge will take them, indeed your Lord knows best those who stray from His path, and He knows best those who receive guidance"
  53,31,"Yes, to God belongs all that is in the heavens and on earth. He rewards those who do wrong, according to their deeds, and He rewards those who do right, with what is best"
  53,32,"Those who avoid great sins and shameful deeds, only falling into small faults, indeed your Lord is ample in forgiveness. He knows you well when He brings you out of the earth, and when you are hidden in your mothers’ wombs. Therefore do not justify yourselves. He knows best who it is that guards against harm"
  53,33,"See the one, who turns back"
  53,34,"Gives a little, then hardens"
  53,35,"What, have they knowledge of the unknown and can they see it"
  53,36,"No, is he not acquainted with what is in the Books of Moses"
  53,37,"And of Abraham, who fulfilled his engagements"
  53,38,"Namely, that no bearer of burdens can bear the burden of another"
  53,39,That human beings can have nothing but what they strive for
  53,40,That their striving will soon come into sight
  53,41,Then they will be rewarded with a reward complete
  53,42,That to your Lord is the final goal
  53,43,That it is He Who grants laughter and tears
  53,44,That it is He Who grants death and life
  53,45,"That He created in pairs, male and female"
  53,46,From a zygote when lodged in its place
  53,47,That He has promised a second creation
  53,48,That it is He Who gives wealth and satisfaction
  53,49,That He is the Lord of Sirius
  53,50,"And that it is He Who caused to perish, the ancient ‘Ad people"
  53,51,"And the Thamud, nor gave them a lease of perpetual life"
  53,52,"And before them, the people of Noah, because they were all most unjust and most insolent transgressors"
  53,53,And He caused to perish the overthrown cities
  53,54,And they have been covered up
  53,55,Then about which of the gifts of your Lord will you dispute
  53,56,"This is a warner, of the series of warners ahead of him"
  53,57,The Ever Approaching draws near
  53,58,None but God can remove it
  53,59,Do you then wonder at this recital
  53,60,And will you laugh and not weep
  53,61,Wasting your time in vanities
  53,62,"But fall down in prostration to God, in worship to Him"